    <!-- FAQ SECTION -->
    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About Metabolism Gummies</h2>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Do metabolism gummies actually work for weight loss?</summary>
      <p>They provide modest metabolic support with clinically studied ingredients like green tea extract (+80 calories/day energy expenditure), chromium (insulin sensitivity), and ACV (blood sugar regulation). However, no supplement creates a calorie deficit on its own. They are a complementary tool, not a primary weight loss solution. Diet and exercise remain the foundation.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What ingredients have the most evidence?</summary>
      <p>Green tea extract (EGCG) has the strongest meta-analysis support for thermogenesis. Chromium picolinate improves insulin sensitivity. ACV has modest evidence for blood sugar regulation. B-vitamins are essential energy metabolism cofactors. Capsaicin (cayenne) increases metabolic rate via TRPV1 activation. Caffeine is a well-established thermogenic but limited in gummy format.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>How long do metabolism gummies take to work?</summary>
      <p>Thermogenic effects (EGCG, caffeine) are measurable within hours but modest. Cumulative benefits — improved energy, stabilized blood sugar, enhanced fat oxidation — become noticeable after 4-8 weeks. Weight management results combined with diet and exercise appear over 8-12 weeks. No metabolism gummy produces rapid weight loss.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Are metabolism gummies safe?</summary>
      <p>Most are safe for healthy adults. Common ingredients (B-vitamins, ACV, green tea) have strong safety profiles. Avoid products with high caffeine or undisclosed stimulant doses. Side effects may include jitteriness or GI discomfort. Consult your physician if taking thyroid, diabetes, or blood-thinning medications, or if pregnant or breastfeeding.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Can I take metabolism gummies with other supplements?</summary>
      <p>Generally yes. Avoid stacking multiple stimulant products. If yours contains chromium, be aware it may enhance blood sugar medication effects. Green tea extract may interact with blood thinners. Always disclose all supplements to your healthcare provider.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What is the difference between metabolism gummies and fat burner pills?</summary>
      <p>Fat burner pills often contain higher stimulant doses (200-300mg caffeine, synephrine, yohimbine). Metabolism gummies use milder, food-derived ingredients at moderate doses. Gummies are better tolerated and more suitable for beginners or stimulant-sensitive individuals. Fat burner pills deliver stronger acute thermogenic effects but with more side effects.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Do B-vitamins actually boost metabolism?</summary>
      <p>B-vitamins are essential cofactors in every energy metabolism pathway. If you are deficient, supplementation meaningfully improves metabolism and reduces fatigue. If already adequate, additional supplementation provides minimal extra benefit. Most impactful for vegans (B12), older adults, and those with restricted diets.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>When should I take metabolism gummies?</summary>
      <p>Morning or early afternoon, aligned with your active hours. If it contains ACV, take before meals for blood sugar benefits. If it contains B-vitamins, morning dosing leverages energy effects during the workday. Avoid stimulant-containing products after 2 PM to prevent sleep disruption.</p>
    </details>

